        <hr noshade size="2" color="#545A7D">
        
         Aye, bloodgills in Lake of Ill Omen are good too, fear one away, other will attack you.  Throw pet at it, darkness it and fear (it WONT go far).  They have LOW hps and are good exp.  Watch out for the fish(barracuda?) in the water.  You dont want one getting on your back while you're fighting gobbies.  You should kill the first goblin fairly quick and the second one will be coming back.  Take him and move to the next group.  In the front there is a gorup of 4, you dont want to pull all of them so be careful.  There's also a spot where a fish (barracuda?) spawns about 30 secs to 1 minute after you kill it.  They're easy like the goblins.  If someone can post the /loc it spawns at, you can continuously kill this thing almost nonstop for a few levels.  When you fear it, it'll onlly go about 5 feet, so a SIMPLE kill that you can play with for quite a while.</P><P> <a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
